From: Daniel Nylander <daniel@danielnylander.se>
Subject: [PATCH] AGI: Guard against integer overflow in LZW allocation

When allocating memory with `count * sizeof(element)`, the
multiplication can overflow on 32-bit systems if count is large enough.
This results in a small allocation followed by out-of-bounds writes
during decompression — a heap buffer overflow.

Add overflow check before allocation.

---
 engines/agi/lzw.cpp | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/engines/agi/lzw.cpp b/engines/agi/lzw.cpp
index abcdef4..1234570 100644
--- a/engines/agi/lzw.cpp
+++ b/engines/agi/lzw.cpp
@@ -XX,6 +XX,12 @@
+	// Guard against integer overflow in allocation
+	if (count > SIZE_MAX / sizeof(element_type)) {
+		warning("LZW: allocation size overflow (count=%u)", count);
+		return nullptr;
+	}
+
 	buffer = (element_type *)malloc(count * sizeof(element_type));
 
-- 
